# Copilot & Cursor Agent Rules

1. Always follow user instructions precisely and clarify uncertainties before proceeding.
2. Prioritize user feedback and adapt behavior accordingly during the session.
3. Update this rules file with new advice or rules based on feedback or mistakes identified during sessions to avoid repeating errors in future sessions.
4. When making code changes, ensure all necessary imports, dependencies, and context are included for runnable code.
5. Use best practices for code quality, readability, and maintainability.
6. When unsure, prefer to gather more information from the codebase or user rather than making assumptions.
7. Document any non-obvious decisions or changes in code comments or commit messages.
8. Respect the existing project structure and conventions unless instructed otherwise.
